frameDefinitions: In this frame a Deformer deforms a Patient possibly against a Resistant_surface such that it undergoes a shape-change from its canonical or original shape into the Configuration, a new shape.
The words in this frame describe the 'fictive' motion of a stationary Road.
An Agent goes to an Event and is present in a relatively non-participatory way.
A salient Subevent has a Pattern of recurrence within a larger Process.
This frame contains words which describe the dimensional extent and Shape of a Substance.
A Theme, which may or may not have a default shape or configuration, goes into a particular shape without being made to do so by an agent.
frameExamples: Ellen <t>crumpled</t> the paper into a ball.
The long mountain road <t>meandered</t> through the woods.
The Angolan guerrillas will <t>attend</t> a September meeting in Zaire.
Tony's fingers tapped <t>rhythmically</t> on the keyboard
She held a <t><fex name='Shape'>square</fex></t> of cloth .
It <t>curled</t> up into a cylinder after laying in the sun.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Deformer</fen> is the one who does the reshaping.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity acted on and that undergoes a change.
The <fen>Cause</fen> is an animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces an effect. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
A state that holds of the <fen>Patient</fen> or a relation that holds among the constituent parts of the <fen>Patient</fen> as a result of the arranging action.
The role <fen>Time</fen> identifies when the <fen>Deformer</fen> intentionally affects the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the <fen>Deformer</fen> intentionally affects the <fen>Patient</fen>.

Any expression which implies a definite starting-point of the <fen>Road</fen>. In prepositional phrases, the prepositional object expresses the starting point of motion. In particles, the starting point of motion is understood from context.
The trajectory that would be followed by one moving on the <fen>Road</fen>.
Any expression which tells where the fictive mover travelling along a <fen>Road</fen> would end up.

A physical path that a virtual moving entity can be imagined to travel along.
<fex name='Road'>The bike trail</fex> <t>zigzagged</t> through the woods.
This frame element is used for expressions which describe a general area in which motion takes place when the motion is understood to be irregular and not to consist of a single linear path.
The configuration formed by the entire <fen>Path</fen> along the <fen>Road</fen>.
The direction in which a 'fictive' mover would travel along a <fen>Road</fen>.

The time when the fictive motion takes place.  This may describe the time when the <fen>Road</fen> or a particular piece of the <fen>Road</fen> existed, or it may implicitly describe the time when an actual motion event occurred on the <fen>Road</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the motion (which is specified by a <fen>Source</fen>, <fen>Path</fen> or <fen>Goal</fen>) is located.
The  <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who chooses to make himself present at the <fen>Event</fen>.
The <fen>Event</fen> is the deliberate set of happenings given at a particular time and place.
When the <fen>Agent</fen> attends the <fen>Event</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> attends the <fen>Event</fen>.
The larger event that is characterized by the recurring Subevents.
The salient, punctual event that is construed as part of a <fen>Process</fen>.
The <fen>Pattern</fen> that can be detected in the recurrence of  the <fen>Subevent</fen>s of the <fen>Process</fen> .
A <fen>Substance</fen> of which pieces can be extracted.
This is the <fen>Shape</fen> that the <fen>Substance</fen> is in.
The <fen>Theme</fen> goes into a particular shape.
The <fen>Result</fen> is the shape the <fen>Theme</fen> becomes.
When the changing into a particular shape occurs.
Where the shape-changing event takes place.
listRoleExamples: <fex>The lieutenant</fex> crushed it angrily with his boot before looking back at Hencke.
Jack plucked the flower out of his morning coat and closed his fist slowly over it , crushing <fex>it</fex> into a pulp.
<fex>The strong winds</fex> deformed the structure of the outhouse.
The lieutenant crushed it angrily with his boot <fex>before looking back at Hencke</fex>.
The Way descends <fex>from the City of the Peak</fex> through a dense forest.
The pass dips <fex>down</fex> about 2000 feet, and then <fex>back up</fex> again.
<fex>Thousands of years ago</fex>, the Roman roads criss-crossed this landscape.
<fex>In the mountains</fex>, Highway 60 winds and swerves a lot, so we lost a couple of hours from my estimate.
The rhythm <fex>of the rain falling on the roof</fex> kept me awake
The music had a driving rhythm
